# --- Google Custom Search (curated-domain discovery — new primary source) ---
# Free tier: 100 queries/day, hard cap with no recovery until the daily
# reset (unlike Scholar's softer/temporary block below) — this is why
# discovery/queryCache.ts caches every raw query result for a week.
# One-time setup (both required together; missing either disables this
# source cleanly, never a hard error):
#   1. Create a free Programmable Search Engine: https://programmablesearchengine.google.com/
#      ("Search the entire web" is fine — site: restriction happens per-query
#      in code via discovery/curatedDomains.ts, not in the PSE config itself)
#   2. Copy its Search Engine ID into GOOGLE_CSE_ID below.
#   3. Get an API key (same Google Cloud project) from
#      https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/overview and put it in
#      GOOGLE_CSE_API_KEY below.
GOOGLE_CSE_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_CSE_ID=

# --- ScholarMCP (Google Scholar discovery — best-effort supplement only) ---
# No API key required. Keep this conservative to reduce throttling risk —
# 800ms is already the default if unset. If you see "Google Scholar blocked
# or challenged this request" in a run's log, Google has temporarily
# rate-limited this network/IP: raise this value (e.g. 1500-2000) and wait a
# while before retrying — there is no faster workaround, and retrying
# immediately risks prolonging the block. A Scholar failure no longer
# aborts the run (see discovery/multiSourceDiscovery.ts) — it just
# contributes zero Scholar candidates for that run.
SCHOLAR_REQUEST_DELAY_MS=800

# --- LLM (analysis layer: relevance scoring, extraction, narrative writing) ---
# Reuses the same NVIDIA-hosted endpoint/model already used in app/'s literature pipeline.
NVIDIA_API_KEY=
LLM_MODEL=meta/llama-3.1-70b-instruct

# --- Role-specialized literature sources ---
# OpenAlex asks for a contact email (politeness, not auth) for higher rate limits.
OPENALEX_MAILTO=
# Unpaywall requires a contact email per their API terms.
UNPAYWALL_EMAIL=
# CORE requires a free API key (https://core.ac.uk/services/api). Optional — pipeline
# degrades gracefully (skips CORE) when unset.
CORE_API_KEY=
# BHL (Biodiversity Heritage Library) requires a free API key. Optional — used for
# historic-literature discovery and OCR full text.
BHL_API_KEY=

# --- Reference data paths (defaults shown; rarely need overriding) ---
# DATA_DIR=./data
# RAW_DIR=./raw
# CATALOG_DIR=./catalog
# WIKI_DIR=./wiki
# OUTPUTS_DIR=./outputs
